Dans le contrôleur :
```typescript
import { ClassSerializerInterceptor, UseInterceptors } from '@nestjs/common';

@Get('products')
@UseInterceptors(ClassSerializerInterceptor)
findAllPublic() {
  const products = this.productsService.findAll();
  return products.map(p => plainToClass(ProductResponseDto, p, { groups: ['public'] }));
}

@Get('admin/products')
@UseInterceptors(ClassSerializerInterceptor)
@Roles('admin')
findAllAdmin() {
  const products = this.productsService.findAll();
  return products.map(p => plainToClass(ProductResponseDto, p, { groups: ['admin'] }));
}
```
Ou utiliser `serialize` dans le service avec `instanceToPlain( dto, { groups: ['admin'] } )`.
